<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-17T08:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-17T08:35:00-05:00" n="609" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.515/97: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-17T17:00:00+03:25">April 17,
                                    1943—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 11:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>394. Millspaugh has been informed concerning desired method of filing
                            application for gold bars and requested to specify type desired.</p>
                        <p>British Legation reports that so far as it knows its proposal is awaiting
                            approval by Washington. There is no change in the matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>